          "text": "Perfect! I have completed the fault localization analysis. Here's a summary of my findings:\n\n## Fault Localization Summary\n\n**Bug Report**: Missing PCI subdevice entries for Intel device 0x2526 (Wireless-AC 9260) with subdevice IDs 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C causing firmware loading failure.\n\n**Root Cause Analysis**:\nThe driver cannot recognize these specific hardware variants because they are not registered in the PCI device ID table. Without these entries, the Linux kernel driver fails to match and initialize the wireless card, preventing firmware from being loaded.\n\n**Buggy File**: `drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c`\n\n**Buggy Structure**: `iwl_hw_card_ids` - the PCI device ID array (line 84)\n\n**Location**: The missing entries should be inserted at lines 595-599, before the existing `0x4034` entry, maintaining hexadecimal order.\n\n**Pattern Analysis**:\n- Other 0x2526 entries with device 9260 use `iwl9260_2ac_cfg` configuration\n- Examples: 0x0210, 0x0214, 0x1010, 0x1210 all use `iwl9260_2ac_cfg`\n- Since the bug mentions \"Wireless-AC 9260 card\", the missing entries should follow this same pattern\n\n**Confidence**: 0.95 - Very high confidence based on clear pattern matching and code structure analysis\n\nThe fault localization result has been written to `/workspace/fault_localization_result.json`.",
